                        <handDesc> 
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p> 
                           <locus from="[1]r" to="[1]v"> ff. [1]r-[1]v </locus>
                                Hand A: the text has been written by a single scribe, in an upright minuscule script, of small size, with some 
                                imbalance produced by larger letters, as <hi rend="italic"> sigma</hi>, <hi rend="italic"> gamma</hi>, <hi rend="italic"> ypsilon</hi>. 
                                It is datable probably to the 14th c., possibly the second half (the script can be compared, for example, 
                                with <bibl>A. Turyn, <hi rend="italic"> Dated Greek Manuscripts of the Thirteenth and Fourteenth Centuries 
                                in the Libraries of Great Britain</hi>, Washington 1980</bibl>, plates 87 dated of 1362, and 88 of 1362/1363). </p>
                        <p>
                                The text is written in black and red ink.</p>
                            </handNote>
                            
                        </handDesc>
                        
