                    <history> 
                        <origin calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1350">
                            On the basis of the script, 
                            the text was written possibly <origDate calendar="gregorian" from="1350" to="1400"> in the second half of the 14th century.</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        
                        <provenance when="1893"> The fragment was part of the Bateman's collection (see the book-plate 
                            on the left pastedown of the binding of the album of fragments Add. 4166: <q> Bateman of Middleton Hall (by Youlgrave) in the
                                County of Derby</q> ); probably the album was owned, in particular, by 
                            <name key="person_v53033345" role="fmo">
                                <persName type="display"> Thomas Bateman (1821-1861)</persName>
                                    <persName type="standard"> Bateman, Thomas, 1821-1861</persName>
                     </name> (see <bibl>R. Rushforth, <hi rend="italic"> The Barrow Knight, the Bristol 
                                        Bibliographer, and a Lost Old English Prayer</hi>, in: Transactions of the Cambridge Bibliographical Society, 13.1, 2004, 
                                        pp. 112-131</bibl>: 112-114).
                            It was sold within the "Bateman heirlooms" sale by Sotheby's on 25th May 1893 (Lot 1528). 
                            MS Add. 4166 was acquired by Quaritch (on the sale see <bibl> Rushforth 2004 </bibl>: 115), and afterwards 
                            came into the possession of the bibliographer <name key="person_v17388260" role="fmo">
                                <persName type="display"> Samuel Sandars (1837-1894)</persName>
                                <persName type="standard"> Sandars, S. (Samuel)</persName>
                     </name>, whose family 
                            originated in Derbyshire.</provenance>
                        
                        <acquisition when="1894"> MS Add. 4166 was bequeathed to the University Library by Samuel Sandars, M.A. of Trinity College, in 1894 
                            (see the book-plate on the left pastedown of the binding of the album Add. 4166).</acquisition>
                        
                    </history>
                    
